Anonymous Sat 06 Mar 2021 12:37:54 No.36857270 Report
Quoted By: >>36858458
>>36857119
There is actually a famous experiment that was started in the 1970s that was inspired by the diversity of dog breeds. The soviet biologist Dmitry Belyayev took a bunch of silver foxes (color morph of the red fox) and separated them into a control group and one group that would be selectively bred based on shortest flight distance (the distance they'd run away if approached). Even though they weren't selectively bred for that, some of them started to develop coat colors, curly tails and floppy ears. It didn't even take many generations and was a huge surprise to the researchers.

So I suppose you can argue (and handwave) for anthro dog "breeds" to arise as a by-product from social circumstances and/or their environment.
